The paper proposes a reinforcement learning approach for query answering over incomplete knowledge graphs, which involves modeling advances to address issues related to false negative supervision and sensitivity to spurious paths. This work is relevant to several sub-fields of computer science, including artificial intelligence (cs.AI), computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), databases (cs.DB), and information retrieval (cs.IR).
